        <content><![CDATA[<h1 class="title topictitle1">Using the NeedIt Form</h1>
<p><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO218083195 BCX0">Use the </span><span class="SpellingError SCXO218083195 BCX0">NeedIt</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO218083195 BCX0"> application to request services and goods from several departments.</span></p>
<ul><li><strong>Legal</strong> </li></ul>
<ul class="steps-unordered"><li class="li step"><strong>Human Resources</strong> </li></ul>
<ul class="steps-unordered"><li class="li step"><strong>Facilities</strong> </li></ul>
<h2 class="title sectiontitle"><span class="TextRun MacChromeBold  BCX0 SCXO25598412" lang="EN-US"><span class="SpellingError  BCX0 SCXO25598412">NeedIt</span><span class="NormalTextRun  BCX0 SCXO25598412"> Form Fields</span></span></h2>
<ol class="steps-ordered"><li class="li step">For new NeedIt records, the <em>Requested for</em> field is pre-populated with your name. If you are opening a NeedIt request for someone else, you can change the value in the <em>Requested for</em> field.</li><li class="li step">The <em>Requested for email</em> field is automatically populated if you change the user in the <em>Requested for</em> field. You can change the <em>Requested for email</em> field value.</li><li class="li step">The choices in the <em>What needed</em> field depend on the value in the<em> Request type</em> field.</li><li class="li step">If the value in the <em>What needed</em> field is Other, the Other field appears. Use the Other field to add a few words about your request.</li><li class="li step">Use the calendar picker in the <em>When needed</em> field to set the due date for the NeedIt request.</li><li class="li step">Use the <em>Short description</em> and <em>Description</em> fields to provide more information about your request.</li></ol>
<div class="note tm-element"><span class="notetitle">Note: <span class="TextRun MacChromeBold SCXO80466776 BCX0" lang="EN-US"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO80466776 BCX0">When creating </span><span class="SpellingError SCXO80466776 BCX0">NeedIt</span><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO80466776 BCX0"> requests, the </span></span><span class="TextRun MacChromeBold SCXO80466776 BCX0" lang="EN-US"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO80466776 BCX0">When needed</span></span><span class="TextRun MacChromeBold SCXO80466776 BCX0" lang="EN-US"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO80466776 BCX0"> date cannot be today or in the past.</span></span></span></div>
<h2 class="title sectiontitle"><span class="TextRun MacChromeBold SCXO220769856 BCX0" lang="EN-US"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO220769856 BCX0">Need More Help?</span></span></h2>
<p><span class="TextRun MacChromeBold SCXO220769856 BCX0" lang="EN-US"><span class="TextRun MacChromeBold SCXO45768066 BCX0" lang="EN-US"><span class="NormalTextRun SCXO45768066 BCX0">You can learn about <a title="form fields" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/paris-platform-user-interface/page/use/using-forms/concept/c_FormFields.html#c_FormFields" target="_blank" rel="noopener">form fields</a> on the ServiceNow docs site.</span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
